<item>
            <title>[WFLY-2741] Single process management operation timeouts</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-2741</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Portion of the parent task related to operation execution within a single process (i.e. not involving intra-process calls in a domain).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Potential points to apply the timeout:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ModelControllerImpl.acquireLock() &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Questionable, as blocking here means waiting for another op, not a problem with the current op&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ModelControllerImpl.awaitContainerMonitor() -&amp;gt; ContainerStateMonitor.await() -&amp;gt; StabilityMonitor.awaitStability()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the typical blocking point in a server op&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; on way in, fail the op&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; on way out (OperationContextImpl.releaseStepLocks()) log a WARN/ERROR&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ModelControllerImpl.awaitContainerStateChangedReport()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; on the way in, before VERIFY&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OperationContextImpl.waitForRemovals()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; on way in, before VERIFY&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; on way out, in handleRollback&lt;br/&gt;
---- problem: this is called repeatedly&lt;/p&gt;</description>
